The paper discusses a random access procedure in uplink massive MIMO systems, which involves utilizing the large number of antennas and inherent timing misalignments. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with the concept of massive MIMO systems, which falls under the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper also discusses collision resolution, which is a common problem in Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), making it a possible sub-category as well.
